iginal Motion Picture Soundtrack) by A. R. Rahman|url=https://music.apple.com/in/album/i-manoharudu-original-motion-picture-soundtrack/953411595|language=en-gb|access-date=2019-11-02}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n== Album credits ==\n'''Backing Vocals'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.arrahman.com/discography_details.aspx?id=272|title=Album Credits for 'I'|last=|first=|date=19 September 2014|work=A. R. Rahman's Official Website|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140922050329/http://www.arrahman.com/discography_details.aspx?id=272|archivedate=22 September 2014|accessdate=19 September 2014}}</ref>\nNivas, [[Santhosh Narayanan]], Deepak, Arjun Chandrasekar, Pooja A. V., Aanchal, [[Maria Roe Vincent]]\n\n[[KM Music Conservatory|K.M.M.C. Choir]] conducted by Neuman Pinto for the song \"Ennodu Nee Irundhal\"\n\n'''Personnel'''\n* [[Guitars]]: [[Keba Jeremiah]]\n* [[Bass (guitar)|Bass]]: Keith Peters, Keba Jeremiah\n* [[Violin]]: Ganesh\n* [[Rhythm|Indian Rhythm]]: T. Raja, Kumar, Neelakandan, Raju, [[A. S. Laxmi Narayanan|Laxminarayan]], Vedachalam\n\n'''Production'''\n* Producer: A. R. Rahman\n* Mastering: S. Sivakumar\n* Chennai Strings Orchestra: V. J. Srinivasamurthy ({{small|at AM Studios, Chennai}})\n* Engineers: {{unbulleted list|Suresh Permal, Srinidhi Venkatesh, Vinay S. Hariharan ({{small|at Panchathan Record Inn, Chennai}}) | Tony Joy, Kevin Doucette ({{small|at Panchathan Hollywood, LA}}) | S. Sivakumar, Kannan Ganpat, Karthik Sekaran, Anantha Krishnan, Pradeep ({{small|at AM Studios, Chennai}})}}\n* Vocal supervision: [[Srinivas (singer)|Srinivas]], Srinidhi Venkatesh\n* Mixing: Kevin Doucette, Suresh Permal | [[P. A. Deepak]] & Ishaan Chhabra for the song \"Merasalaayiten (Remix)\"\n* Additional programming: [[Ranjit Barot]], [[Pravin Mani]], T. R. Krishana Chetan, Marc, Hentry Kuruvilla | Soumya Sejpal for the song \"Ladio\"\n* Music co-ordinators: Noell James, Vijay Mohan Iyer\n* Musicians' fixer: R. Samidurai\n\n== See also ==\n*[[I (film)|I]]\n*[[A. R. Rahman discography]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{A. R. Rahman}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:I (soundtrack)}}\n[[Category:2014 soundtracks]]\n[[Category:A. R. Rahman soundtracks]]\n[[Category:Tamil film soundtracks]]\n[[Category:Sony Music India soundtracks]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2014}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = I (Original Motion Picture Soundtrack)\n| type         = Soundtrack\n| artist       = [[A. R. Rahman]]\n| cover        = I (2014 film) OST.jpg\n| alt          = \n| caption      = Digital Soundtrack Cover Art\n| released     = 12 September 2014 (Original)<br/>31 December 2014 (Hindi & Telugu)\n| recorded     = 2012\u20142014<br/>[[Panchathan Record Inn and AM Studios]], [[Chennai]]<br/>Panchathan Hollywood Studios, [[Los Angeles]]\n| venue        = \n| studio       = \n| genre        = \n| length       = 33:56\n| language     = {{flatlist|\n*[[Tamil language|Tamil]]\n*[[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n*[[Hindi language|Hindi]]\n}}\n| label        = {{flatlist|\n*[[Sony Music India|Sony Music]]\n*[[T-Series (company)|T-Series]] (Hindi)}}\n| producer     = [[A.R.Rahman]]\n| prev_title   = [[Kaaviya Thalaivan (soundtrack)|Kaaviya Thalaivan]]\n| prev_year    = 2014\n| next_title   = [[Lingaa (soundtrack)|Lingaa]]\n| next_year    = 2014\n| misc         = {{Singles\n | name        = I\n | type        = soundtrack\n | single1     = [[Pookkalae Sattru Oyivedungal]]\n | single1date = {{Start date|df=yes|2014|09|10}} (Original)<br/>{{Start date|df=yes|2014|12|26}} (Hindi)<br/>{{Start date|df=yes|2014|12|30}} (Telugu)\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''I''''' is the [[soundtrack album]] to the 2015 Indian [[Romance film|romantic]]  [[thriller film]] of the [[I (film)|same name]] written and directed by [[S. Shankar]]. [[A. R. Rahman]] had composed the original songs and background score for the film.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/tamil-movie-i-hits-the-floor/271446-71-174.html |title=Shankar's next Tamil movie 'I' hits the floor |work=[[CNN-IBN|IBNLive]] |date=15 July 2012 |access-date=11 September 2014 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6SYLNLSCg?url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/tamil-movie-i-hits-the-floor/271446-71-174.html |archive-date=13 September 2014 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> The album consists of seven tracks, which include a [[remix]] and a [[reprise]].\n\nRecording of the songs began in 2012 and was completed by 2014. Songs in the film vary in genre like [[Electronic dance music|EDM]], [[Bhangra (music)|bhangra]], [[Op\u00e9ra (genre)|opera]], urban. The original and Hindi version of the soundtrack has youth oriented voices. The original version of the album was released on 6 September 2014.<ref name=\"thehindu\">{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/arnold-schwarzenegger-to-attend-ai-audio-launch-in-chennai/article6385984.ece|title=Arnold Schwarzenegger to attend \u2018Ai\u2019 audio launch|work=[[The Hindu]]|date=6 September 2014|access-date=11 September 2014|archive-url=https://archive.today/20140911120424/http://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/arnold-schwarzenegger-to-attend-ai-audio-launch-in-chennai/article6385984.ece|url-status=live|archive-date=11 September 2014}}</ref>\n\nThe audio was launched at a grand function at the [[Jawaharlal Nehru Stadium (Chennai)|Jawaharlal Nehru Indoor Stadium]], Chennai on 12 September 2014, with [[Arnold Schwarzenegger]] as the Chief Guest. The Hindi version of the album was released at a promotional event held in [[PVR Cinemas|PVR]], [[Mumbai]] on 31 December 2014. The Telugu version of the album was [[Music download|released digitally]] on the same day.\n\nThe soundtrack as well as the score received a very positive critical reception and it was declared one of the top twenty best selling albums of 2014 by [[ITunes Store|iTunes India]]. At the [[63rd Filmfare Awards South|2016 Filmfare Awards]], A. R. Rahman won the [[Filmfare Award for Best Music Director \u2013 Tamil|Filmfare Award for Best Music Director]] whereas lyricist [[Madhan Karky]] won [[Filmfare Award for Best Lyricist \u2013 Tamil|Filmfare Award for Best Lyricist]] for his lyrics to the song \"[[Pookkalae Sattru Oyivedungal]]\". Shreya Ghoshal was nominated for the same track under [[Filmfare Award for Best Female Playback Singer \u2013 Tamil|Filmfare Award for Best Female Playback Singer]]. Lyricist Kabilan was nominated for Filmfare Award for Best Lyricist for the track \"Ennodu Nee Irundhaal\". However, Sid Sriram won the [[Filmfare Award for Best Male Playback Singer \u2013 Tamil|Filmfare Award for Best Male Playback Singer]] for the song.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.filmfare.com/news/winners-of-the-63rd-britannia-filmfare-awards-south-13996.html|title=Winners of the 63rd Britannia Filmfare Awards (South)|website=filmfare.com|access-date=2016-06-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170704080550/http://www.filmfare.com/news/winners-of-the-63rd-britannia-filmfare-awards-south-13996.html|archive-date=4 July 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n== Development ==\n[[A. R. Rahman]] was selected to compose the original songs and background score for the film.<ref>{{cite web|author=Ramanujam, Srinivasa|date=2 July 2014|url=http://www.dailymotion.com/video/x2ef5fs_i-pookkale-satru-oivedu-video-song-tamil_shortfilms|title=Anirudh sings for Shankar\u2019s 'Ai'|work=[[The Hindu]]|access-date=26 August 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150114061804/http://www.dailymotion.com/video/x2ef5fs_i-pookkale-satru-oivedu-video-song-tamil_shortfilms|url-status=live|archive-date=14 January 2015}}</ref> In early July 2012, singer [[Vijay Prakash]] recorded the track \"Pareshanayya\" (Telugu version of \"Mersalayitten\").<ref>{{cite news | url= http://ibnlive.in.com/news/director-shankar-to-start-i-with-vikram/267401-71-180.html |title=Director Shankar to start 'I' with Vikram |publisher=[[CNN-IBN|IBNLive]] |date=22 June 2012 |accessdate=15 July 2012}}</ref> In January 2013, the song \"Aila Aila\" was recorded. Karky called it as the \"most challenging song\" he had ever worked on.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-01-12/news-interviews/36295868_1_madhan-karky-vikram-and-amy-jackson-shankar |title=Madhan Karky's challenging song |newspaper=[[The Times of India]] |date=12 January 2013 |access-date=12 January 2013 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6SYLjxyGp?url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/tamil/news-interviews/Madhan-Karkys-challenging-song/articleshow/17995071.cms?referral=PM |archive-date=13 September 2014 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> As some part of the film's story is about [[Model (people)|modeling]], his team created a compilation of six-seven [[Advertising|commercials]] that play to this song. According to Karky, \"The lyrics of Aila Aila was the most difficult to pen as each line will have two different meanings, one is what you hear and one is what you are going to watch on the screen\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tamilsonglyrics.org/movies/f-j/i/|title=I Tamil Movie Songs lyrics|accessdate=2015-03-11|publisher=tamilsonglyrics}}</ref><ref name=icl>{{cite web|url=http://cinemalead.com/news-id-exclusive-scoop-i-making-video-16-09-146058.htm|title=AN EXCLUSIVE SCOOP ON 'I' AND ITS MAKING VIDEO|work=Cinemalead|accessdate=17 September 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140917114416/http://cinemalead.com/news-id-exclusive-scoop-i-making-video-16-09-146058.htm|archivedate=17 September 2014}}</ref> The five and a half minute track blends genres like [[pop music|pop]], [[bhangra (music)|bhangra]], [[op\u00e9ra comique]] elements and [[Electronic music|electronic beats]].<ref>{{cite news | url= http://www.thehindu.com/features/metroplus/article6475411.ece|title=Aditya goes \u2018Aila\u2026\u2019|newspaper=The Hindu|first=Apoorva|last=Srivathi|date=7 October 2014|accessdate=7 October 2014}}</ref> In an interview with ''[[The Hindu]]'', [[S. Shankar]] stated that he wanted unusual music for ''I'' with extensive experimentation. He called the experimentation most evident in this track especially the operatic part. The song slightly touches underlying feeling of romance.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-metroplus/i-feel-i-have-to-outdo-my-last-film/article6494242.ece|title=\u2018I feel I have to outdo my last film\u2019|work=The Hindu|date=13 October 2014|accessdate=15 October 2014}}</ref> Portions of the track \"Ennodu Nee Irundhaal\" sung only by [[Sunitha Sarathy]] were recorded on 14 February 2013.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-02-14/news-interviews/37099349_1_release-records-download |title=AR Rahman records one for Shankar's I |newspaper=[[The Times of India]] |date=14 February 2013 |access-date=14 February 2013 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6SYLk65Ol?url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/tamil/news-interviews/AR-Rahman-records-one-for-Shankars-I/articleshow/18496215.cms?referral=PM |archive-date=13 September 2014 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> Rahman was supposed to have sung \"Ennodu Nee Irundhaal\" but chose Sid Sriram because the latter sang it well and Rahman felt that Sriram didn't earn the deserving recognition through track \"Adiye\" from ''[[Kadal (soundtrack)|Kadal]]'', thus gave a second opportunity.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-14/vasantha-balan-spills-the-beans-on-a-r-rahman.html|title=An interesting story behind I's 'Ennodu Nee Irundhal'|work=Behindwoods|date=6 October 2014|accessdate=6 October 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006112815/http://behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-14/vasantha-balan-spills-the-beans-on-a-r-rahman.html|archivedate=6 October 2014}}</ref> Lyricist Madhan Karky's third song in the film was recorded by mid \u2013 September 2013.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://twitter.com/madhankarky/status/380937152567070720 |title=Recorded my 3rd song for #Ai recently. |publisher=[[Twitter]] |date=21 September 2013 |access-date=21 September 2013 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6SYLknlT9?url=https://twitter.com/madhankarky/status/380937152567070720 |archive-date=13 September 2014 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> In May 2014, Rahman through his [[bulletin board system]] of [[Reddit]] stated that the film songs have more youth-oriented voices.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/arrahman/status/468624321519173633 |title=I am Academy Award winning composer A.R. Rahman. Ask me anything |work=[[Twitter]] |date=19 May 2014 |access-date=1 July 2014 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6SYLlfzRv?url=https://twitter.com/arrahman/status/468624321519173633 |archive-date=13 September 2014 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> The track \"Mersalaayiten\" was recorded by [[Anirudh Ravichander]] and [[Neeti Mohan]] in the span of July \u2013 August 2014.<ref>{{cite web|author=Sundar, Priyanka |date=8 August 2014 |url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/140808/entertainment-kollywood/article/language-no-barrier-neeti-mohan |title=Language no barrier for Neeti Mohan |work=[[Deccan Chronicle]] |access-date=29 August 2014 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6SYLmAaeG?url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/140808/entertainment-kollywood/article/language-no-barrier-neeti-mohan |archive-date=13 September 2014 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/Entertainment/Tamil/Music/Kolaveri-boy-sings-for-AR-Rahman-in-Shankars-Ai/articleshow/37576447.cms |title=Kolaveri boy sings for AR Rahman in Shankar's Ai |newspaper=[[The Times of India]] |date=3 July 2014 |access-date=3 July 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140812125203/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/music/Kolaveri-boy-sings-for-AR-Rahman-in-Shankars-Ai/articleshow/37576447.cms |archive-date=12 August 2014 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> On 4 July 2014, the recording of all the songs for both the versions \u2013 the original Tamil version and the dubbed Telugu version were completed.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/Entertainment/Tamil/Music/AR-Rahman-delivers-Ai-tunes/articleshow/37758903.cms |title=AR Rahman delivers 'Ai' tunes |newspaper=[[The Times of India]] |date=4 July 2014 |access-date=8 July 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140705045701/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/music/AR-Rahman-delivers-Ai-tunes/articleshow/37758903.cms |archive-date=5 July 2014 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url = http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/music/A-R-Rahman-wraps-up-scoring-tunes-for-Shankars-Manoharudu/articleshow/37761162.cms|title = AR Rahman wraps up scoring tunes for Shankar's 'Manoharudu'|newspaper=[[The Times of India]]|date=4 July 2014|accessdate=8 July 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140713112648/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/Entertainment/Telugu/Music/A-R-Rahman-wraps-up-scoring-tunes-for-Shankars-Manoharudu/articleshow/37761162.cms|archivedate=13 July 2014 }}</ref> [[Pravin Mani]] was involved in post-production of the album for two months. He was recruited for the work of recording [[Ancillary market|ancillaries]] and corrections.<ref>{{cite news | url= http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-music-director/pravin-mani/an-interview-with-composer-musician-pravin-mani.html|title=MUSIC DIRECTOR PRAVIN MANI INTERVIEW - \"'AI' IS GOING TO BE A KICK-ASS ALBUM\"|author=Rabindran, Dilani|work=Behindwoods|date=21 August 2014|accessdate=22 August 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140905052442/http://behindwoods.com/tamil-music-director/pravin-mani/an-interview-with-composer-musician-pravin-mani.html|archivedate=5 September 2014 }}</ref> Madhan Karky explained the meanings of the Tamil words he had used in the song \"Ladio\" on his [[Twitter]] page.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-14/madhan-karky-on-ladio.html|title=Shankar's 'I' popularizes Tamil!|work=Behindwoods|date=18 September 2014|accessdate=18 September 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140918073922/http://behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-14/madhan-karky-on-ladio.html|archivedate=18 September 2014}}</ref>\n\n== Release ==\n<!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:Shankars I Audio Launch Still.jpg|thumb|Vikram performing the song \"Ennodu Nee Irundhaal\" in his beast get-up from the film. It took 3 - 4 hours for Vikram to apply the make - up required for the performance.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/Vikram-stuns-everyone-with-beast-get-up/articleshow/42563458.cms|title=Vikram stuns everyone with beast get-up|work=[[The Times of India]]|date=16 September 2014|accessdate=16 September 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140916005239/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/Vikram-stuns-everyone-with-beast-get-up/articleshow/42563458.cms?|archivedate=16 September 2014}}</ref>]] -->\nOn 24 March 2014, [[Sony Music India]] acquired the audio rights of the film.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-14/vikram-amy-jackson-starrer-ai-director-shankars-magnum-opus-post-enthiran-delivered-finally.html|title=Shankar's 'Ai' is finally ready|work=Behindwoods|date=4 July 2014|accessdate=29 August 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140903092518/http://behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-14/vikram-amy-jackson-starrer-ai-director-shankars-magnum-opus-post-enthiran-delivered-finally.html|archivedate=3 September 2014 }}</ref> The official soundtrack album cover of the film was released on 6 September 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.moviecrow.com/News/5629/shankars--i--title-look|title=Shankar's 'I' title look|work=Moviecrow|date=9 September 2014|accessdate=11 September 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140911152323/http://www.moviecrow.com/News/5629/shankars--i--title-look|archivedate=11 September 2014 }}</ref> The audio launch was planned for a release in [[Canada]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/music/Ais-audio-launch-to-be-held-in-Canada/articleshow/33560770.cms |title=Ai\u2019s audio launch to be held in Canada? |work=[[The Times of India]] |date=11 April 2014 |access-date=29 August 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140414044931/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/music/Ais-audio-launch-to-be-held-in-Canada/articleshow/33560770.cms |archive-date=14 April 2014 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> but the film's producer, [[Venu Ravichandran]], asserted that the music of the Tamil version would be released at a grand event at the [[Jawaharlal Nehru Stadium (Chennai)|Nehru Indoor Stadium]] in [[Chennai]] on 12 September 2014.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/Arnold-Jackie-Chan-come-together-for-Shankars-Ai/articleshow/40914556.cms |title=Arnold, Jackie Chan come together for Shankar's 'Ai' |newspaper=[[The Times of India]] |date=26 August 2014 |access-date=26 August 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140827111539/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/Arnold-Jackie-Chan-come-together-for-Shankars-Ai/articleshow/40914556.cms |archive-date=27 August 2014 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> On 1 September 2014, [[Arnold Schwarzenegger]] confirmed himself as an invitee at the forthcoming event.,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/regional/arnold-schwarzenegger-to-attend-tamil-film-ai-s-audio-launch-in-chennai/article1-1260951.aspx|title=Arnold Schwarzenegger to attend Tamil film Ai's audio launch in Chennai?|work=[[Hindustan Times]]|date=5 September 2014|accessdate=5 September 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140912181628/http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/regional/arnold-schwarzenegger-to-attend-tamil-film-ai-s-audio-launch-in-chennai/article1-1260951.aspx|archivedate=12 September 2014 }}</ref> also Kannada actor and singer [[Puneeth Rajkumar]] and Telugu actor [[Rana Daggubati]] was as chief guests.<ref>[https://www.filmibeat.com/tamil/news/2014/arnold-walked-out-i-audio-launch-midway/articlecontent-pf67221-159634.html]</ref> Ravichandran said Rahman would present the songs in a fashion similar to a live music concert.<ref name=\"TOII\">{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/Arnold-wants-to-Chief-Minisiter-Jayalalitha/articleshow/42274878.cms |author=M. Suganth |title=Arnold wants to Chief Minisiter Jayalalitha |work=[[The Times of India]] |date=12 September 2014 |access-date=12 September 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140912160104/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/Arnold-wants-to-Chief-Minisiter-Jayalalitha/articleshow/42274878.cms |archive-date=12 September 2014 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nInternational bubble artist Ana Yang, wife of the 16-time [[Guinness World Records|Guinness World Record holder]], [[Fan Yang (artist)|Fan Yang]], performed as part of the event. [[Weta Workshop]] artists who have worked on the film would provided the makeup for the background dancers, who delivered the performances wearing the actual costumes from the respective songs. A fashion show by the film's costume designer took place.<ref name = TOII/> A rough cut version of the song \"Merasalaayiten\" leaked onto the internet a day prior to the music launch.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-14/bad-and-good-for-anirudhs-upcoming-releases.html|title='Kaththi' & 'Ai' - The Bad and The Good|work=Behindwoods|date=14 September 2014|accessdate=14 September 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140914130224/http://behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-14/bad-and-good-for-anirudhs-upcoming-releases.html|archivedate=14 September 2014}}</ref>\n\n=== Original version ===\n[[Bobby Simha]] and singer [[Chinmayi]] hosted the audio launch.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://photos.filmibeat.com/tamil-events/shankar-s-i-audio-launch/photos-c22-e49200-p493635.html|title=Shankar's 'I' Audio Launch Photos|last=|first=|date=13 September 2014|work=[[Oneindia.in|Oneindia Entertainment]]|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140919104837/http://photos.filmibeat.com/tamil-events/shankar-s-i-audio-launch/photos-c22-e49200-p493635.html|archivedate=19 September 2014|accessdate=13 September 2014}}</ref> [[Anirudh Ravichander]], [[Karthik (singer)|Karthik]], [[Keba Jeremiah]], [[Neeti Mohan]], [[Haricharan]], [[Natalie Di Luccio]], [[A. R. Rahman]], [[Amy Jackson]] and [[Vikram (actor)|Vikram]] were part of the stage performances.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://photos.filmibeat.com/tamil-events/shankar-s-i-audio-launch/49200.html|title=Shankar's 'I' Audio Launch Photos|last=|first=|date=13 September 2014|work=[[Oneindia.in|Oneindia Entertainment]]|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140919104511/http://photos.filmibeat.com/tamil-events/shankar-s-i-audio-launch/49200.html|archivedate=19 September 2014|accessdate=13 September 2014}}</ref> The team from [[Weta Workshop]] was introduced after the song \"Ennodu Nee Irundhaal\" was performed.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/jovial-arnie-teases-shankar/article6413849.ece?secpage=true&secname=entertainment|title=Jovial Arnie teases Shankar|author=Subramanian, Karthik|first=|date=13 September 2014|work=[[The Hindu]]|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140916050743/http://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/jovial-arnie-teases-shankar/article6413849.ece?secpage=true&secname=entertainment|archivedate=16 September 2014|accessdate=13 September 2014}}</ref> In addition to the songs from the soundtrack album, Rahman also performed a few tracks from his previous compositions, which were \"Oorvasi Oorvasi\", \"[[Chikku Bukku Rayile]]\", \"[[Ottagathai Kattiko]]\", \"Muqabala\", \"Petta Rap\", \"Maya Machindra\", \"[[Shakalaka Baby]]\", \"Girlfriend\", \"Colombus Columbus\", \"Athiradi Kaalam\" and \"[[Irumbile Oru Irudhaiyam]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/music/Shankars-I-audio-launched/articleshow/42597885.cms|title=Shankar's 'I' audio launched|last=|first=|date=13 September 2014|work=[[The Times of India]]|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140916053601/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/music/Shankars-I-audio-launched/articleshow/42597885.cms|archive-date=16 September 2014|access-date=13September 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n== Critical reception ==\n=== Songs ===\nThe album received very positive reviews upon release. Critic [[Baradwaj Rangan]] for ''[[The Hindu]]'' called the soundtrack \"wholly individual\" that liberates A. R. Rahman. He felt, \"The soundtrack that sets Rahman apart. At his most playful, he\u2019s capable of synthesising sound and tunesmanship to produce music that\u2019s the equivalent of a modern-art mural. You may not want it on your wall, but this isn\u2019t about wanting it on your wall.\"<ref>{{cite web|author=[[Baradwaj Rangan|Rangan, Baradwaj]]|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/metroplus/thoughts-on-ar-rahmans-gloriously-fun-and-wholly-individual-soundtrack-for-the-new-shankar-film-i/article6419639.ece|title=I, A. R. Rahman|work=[[The Hindu]]|date=17 September 2014|accessdate=18 September 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140918073121/http://www.thehindu.com/features/metroplus/thoughts-on-ar-rahmans-gloriously-fun-and-wholly-individual-soundtrack-for-the-new-shankar-film-i/article6419639.ece|archivedate=18 September 2014 }}</ref> ''[[Sify]]'' said, \"Despite the fact it is not among Isaipuyal\u2019s greater works, \u2019I\u2019 still has 2-3 numbers that are bound to get stuck in our playlists. The simpler tunes like \"Ennodu Nee Irundhaal\" and \"Pookale Satru Oyvedungal\" are here to stay while the peppy \"Mersalaayiten\" and the Shankar-esque \"Aila Aila\" are bound to get enriched by the visuals.\" and rated the album 3.5 out of 5.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/audio-review-i-news-tamil-ojpk7rajbcieh.html |title='I' audio review |work=[[Sify]] |date=15 September 2014 |access-date=18 September 2014 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6SfvRQKJi?url=http://www.sify.com/movies/audio-review-i-news-tamil-ojpk7rajbcieh.html |archive-date=18 September 2014 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }} {{Rating|3.5|5}}</ref> ''Behindwoods'' chose \"Merasalaayiten\", \"Pookkalae Sattru Oyivedungal\" and the track \"Ennodu Nee Irudhaal\" as well as its reprise as the album's picks and gave a rating of 3.5 out of 5, concluding that \"Rahman & Shankar are back to doing what they do best, churn out chart busters !\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://behindwoods.com/tamil-movies/i/i-songs-review.html|title='I' SONGS REVIEW|last=|first=|date=12 September 2014|work=Behindwoods|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140915055539/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/music/I-songs-tops-iTunes-charts/articleshow/42511201.cms|archive-date=15 September 2014|access-date=12 September 2014|df=dmy-all}} {{Rating|3.5|5}}</ref> Vipin of ''Music Aloud'' stated, \"Three winning songs in a half-and-half soundtrack from A R Rahman. Still would rate in the lower half of the ARR-Shankar repertory\".<ref name=\"Music Aloud\">{{cite web|url=http://www.musicaloud.com/2014/09/17/i-music-review-tamil-movie-soundtrack/|title=I \u2013 Music Review (Tamil Movie Soundtrack)|author=Vipin|first=|date=14 September 2014|work=Music Aloud|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140917115555/http://www.musicaloud.com/2014/09/17/i-music-review-tamil-movie-soundtrack/|archivedate=17 September 2014|accessdate=14 September 2014}} {{Rating|8|10}}</ref> However, he called \"Pookkalae Sattru Oyivedungal\" as \"the best of the soundtrack, a charming melody\", and gave the album a rating of 8 out of 10.<ref name=\"Music Aloud\" />\n<ref>{{cite web|url=http://coolmusicz.com/download/index.php?dir=Tamil_Mp3_Songs/Tamil_Yearly_Hits_Mp3_Songs/2014_Tamil_Movies_Mp3_Songs/I&sort=0&ciview=1|title=I Tamil Movie Songs|accessdate=2015-02-22|publisher=coolmusicz}}</ref>\n\n=== Background score ===\nWriting the critical reception for ''[[Firstpost]]'', Latha Srinivasan stated, \"Shankar has done justice to A.R. Rahman\u2019s tunes and that\u2019s a visual treat in the film.\"<ref>{{cite news|url = http://www.firstpost.com/bollywood/i-review-vikrams-the-only-good-thing-about-this-film-shankar-has-lost-his-magic-touch-2047159.html|title = I review: Vikram's the only good thing about this film, Shankar has lost his magic touch|date = 15 January 2015|accessdate = 15 January 2015|work = [[Firstpost]]|last = Srinivasan|first = Latha}}</ref> Rachel Saltz of ''[[The New York Times]]'' wrote called it a score that 'engage ones senses', further noting, \"''I'' could easily be a silent movie\u2014though a noisy one, with a boom-boom score by A.R. Rahman that signals at each turn how the audience should feel, and with flurries of drums, speeds the film along.\"<ref>{{cite news|url = https://www.nytimes.com/2015/01/15/movies/i-a-tamil-film-by-shankar-starring-vikram.html?_r=0|title = Brawls, Biceps and Morphing Cellphones|date = 15 January 2015|accessdate = 15 January 2015|newspaper = The New York Times|last = Saltz|first = Rachel}}</ref>'' [[Telugu diaspora|Gulte]]'' called, Rahman's music 'average', comparing it its standards to his previous works done for Shankar's films.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.gulte.com/moviereviews/439/I-AI-Movie-Review|title = I (AI)|date = 14 January 2015|accessdate = 15 January 2015|website = |publisher = |last = |first = }}</ref> Nandini Ramnath at ''Scroll'' writes that the film has, \"AR Rahman\u2019s least memorable scores with background music set at the level that reads 'This has the potential of damaging eardrums.'\"<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://scroll.in/article/700582/Film-review:-In-%E2%80%98I%E2%80%99,-an-eye-for-an-eye-makes-director-Shankar-go-blind|title = Film review: In \u2018I\u2019, an eye for an eye makes director Shankar go blind|date = 15 January 2015|accessdate = 15 January 2015|website = |publisher = Scroll.in|last = Ramnath|first = Nandini}}</ref> An [[Indo-Asian News Service|''IANS'']]<nowiki/>review mentions, \"A.R. Rahman's score to the film doesn't make much of a difference but for remaining mostly soothing and melodic.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/i-big-is-not-always-great-ians-tamil-movie-review-115011400828_1.html|title = 'I' - big is not always great (IANS Tamil Movie Review)|date = 15 January 2015|accessdate = 15 January 2015|website = IANS|publisher = Business Standard|last = |first = }}</ref> Subramanian Harikumar of ''Bollywood Life'' stated, \"The songs, composed by Rahman, are brilliant, especially Tum Todo Na (Ennodu Nee Irunthaal) song will leave you mesmerised. A great background score from AR Rahman.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.bollywoodlife.com/south-gossip/i-movie-review-shankar-delivers-a-winner-yet-again-riding-high-on-vikrams-brilliant-performance/|title = I movie review: Shankar delivers a winner yet again riding high on Vikram\u2019s brilliant performance|date = 15 January 2015|accessdate = 15 January 2015|website = |publisher = Bollywood Life|last = |first = }}</ref> Suhani Singh for ''[[India Today]]'''' ''writes, \"Music by A.R. Rahman is top class! He has obviously given his best to match up to Shankar's vision.\"<ref>{{cite magazine|url = http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/movie-review-watch-i-for-shankars-vision-&-vikrams-acting/1/413475.html|title = Movie review: I|date = 15 January 2015|accessdate = 15 January 2015|magazine = India Today|last = Singh|first = Suhani}}</ref> R. Vishal at ''[[United Internet]]'' ''wrote'','' \"The songs fail to allure the viewer in the way Shankar\u2019s previous movies have.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url = http://www.india.com/showbiz/i-tamil-movie-review-vikrams-magnificent-performance-let-down-by-contrived-plot-249062/ |title = 'I' Tamil movie review: Vikram's magnificent performance let down by contrived plot |last = |first = |date = 15 January 2015 |website = |publisher = India.com (United Internet) |accessdate = 15 January 2015}}</ref> For ''[[Bangalore Mirror]]'', R. S. Prakash stated, \"A R Rahman has been the composer of all of Shankar's directorial ventures, but here Rahman seems to have been in a hurry to wrap up as none of the songs are effective.\"<ref>{{cite news|url = http://www.bangaloremirror.com/entertainment/reviews/Movie-review-I/articleshow/45889959.cms|title = Movie review: I|date = 15 January 2015|accessdate = 15 January 2015|newspaper = Bangalore Mirror|last = Prakash|first = RS}}</ref> Surabhi Redkar for ''[[Koimoi]]'' writes, \"A R Rahman\u2019s music too does not turn out endearing and overall during the songs.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.koimoi.com/reviews/i-review/|title = I Review|date = 16 January 2015|accessdate = 16 January 2015|website = |publisher = Koimoi|last = Redkar|first = Surabhi}}</ref> Writing for ''[[Mumbai Mirror]]'', Rahul Desai praised the score in film, calling it 'throbbing hours of an operatic musical'.<ref>{{cite news|url = http://www.mumbaimirror.com/entertainment/bollywood/Film-review-I/articleshow/45904711.cms|title = Film review: I|date = 16 January 2015|accessdate = 16 January 2015|newspaper = Mumbai Mirror|last = Desai|first = Rahul}}</ref> Critic based at ''[[Bollywood Hungama]]'' felt, \"The film suffers in the music department (A. R. Rahman), wherein the songs seem to be thrusted into the film's situation.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/criticreview/id/1227736|title = I|date = 16 January 2015|accessdate = 16 January 2015|website = Bollywood Hungama News Network|publisher = [[Bollywood Hungama]]|last = |first = }}</ref>\n\n== Track list ==\n===Tamil===\nThe official track listing of the original version was released by [[Sony Music India|Sony Music South]] on 10 September 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailymotion.com/video/x2ef5fs_i-pookkale-satru-oivedu-video-song-tamil_shortfilms|title=Here's the official track list of Shankar Shanmugham's 'I' in A.R. Rahman's music|last=|first=|date=10 September 2014|work=[[Twitter]]|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140913131632/https://twitter.com/SonyMusicSouth/status/510762539894853632|archivedate=13 September 2014|accessdate=10 September 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://coolmusicz.com/download/index.php?dir=Tamil_Mp3_Songs/Tamil_Yearly_Hits_Mp3_Songs/2014_Tamil_Movies_Mp3_Songs/I&sort=0&ciview=1|title=I Tamil Songs|accessdate=2015-02-22|publisher=coolmusicz.com}}</ref>\n{{tracklist\n| headline        = ''I'' (Original Motion Picture Soundtrack) - Original version\n| extra_column    = Singer(s)\n| total_length    = 33:56\n| title1          = Mersalaayitten\n| lyrics1         = [[Kabilan (Lyricist)|Kabilan]]\n| extra1          = [[Anirudh Ravichander]], [[Neeti Mohan]]\n| length1         = 05:00\n| title2          = Ennodu Nee Irundhaal\n| lyrics2         = [[Kabilan (lyricist)|Kabilan]]\n| extra2          = [[Sid Sriram]], [[Sunitha Sarathy]]\n| length2         = 05:52\n| title3          = Ladio\n| lyrics3         = [[Madhan Karky]] \n| extra3          = [[Nikhita Gandhi]]\n| length3         = 04:42\n| title4          = [[Pookkalae Sattru Oyivedungal]]\n| lyrics4         = [[Madhan Karky]]\n| extra4          = [[Haricharan]], [[Shreya Ghoshal]]\n| length4         = 05:08\n| title5          = Aila Aila\n| lyrics5         = [[Madhan Karky]]\n| extra5          = Aditya Rao, [[Natalie Di Luccio]]\n| length5         = 05:34\n| title6          = Ennodu Nee Irundhaal (Reprise)\n| lyrics6         = [[Kabilan (lyricist)|Kabilan]]\n| extra6    