==Records and statistics==\n===Final===\n====Team====\n\n*'''Most wins:''' 36: \n**[[Thurles Sarsfields GAA|Thurles Sarsfields]] (1887, 1904, 1906, 1907, 1908, 1909, 1911, 1929, 1935, 1936, 1938, 1939, 1942, 1944, 1945, 1946, 1952, 1955, 1956, 1957, 1958, 1959, 1961, 1962, 1963, 1964, 1965, 1974, 2005, 2009, 2010, 2012, 2014, 2015, 2016, 2017)\n*'''Most consecutive wins:''' 5:\n**[[Thurles Sarsfields GAA|Thurles Sarsfields]] (1955, 1956, 1957, 1958, 1959)\n**[[Thurles Sarsfields GAA|Thurles Sarsfields]] (1961, 1962, 1963, 1964, 1965)\n*'''Most appearances in a final:''' 46:\n**[[Thurles Sarsfields GAA|Thurles Sarsfields]] (1887, 1894, 1904, 1906, 1907, 1908, 1909, 1911, 1929, 1935, 1936, 1938, 1939, 1942, 1944, 1945, 1946, 1952, 1955, 1956, 1957, 1958, 1959, 1960, 1961, 1962, 1963, 1964, 1965, 1968, 1970, 1979, 1992, 2000, 2001, 2002, 2003, 1974, 2005, 2009, 2010, 2012, 2014, 2015, 2016, 2017)\n*'''Most appearances in a final without ever winning:''' 5\n** [[Lorrha-Dorrha GAA|Lorrha]] (1905, 1948, 1956, 1966, 1984)\n*'''Most appearances in a final without losing (streak):''' 21 \n**[[Thurles Sarsfields GAA|Thurles Sarsfields]] (1904, 1906, 1907, 1908, 1909, 1911, 1929, 1935, 1936, 1938, 1939, 1942, 1944, 1945, 1946, 1952, 1955, 1956, 1957, 1958, 1959)\n*'''Most defeats:''' 11\n**[[Roscrea GAA|Roscrea]] (1936, 1945, 1954, 1963, 1967, 1971, 1976, 1978, 1981, 1982, 1985)\n\n====Individual====\n\n*'''Most wins by a player:''' 14, [[Mickey Byrne]] ([[Thurles Sarsfields GAA|Thurles Sarsfields]]) (1944, 1945, 1946, 1952, 1955, 1956, 1957, 1958, 1959, 1961, 1962, 1963, 1964, 1965)\n\n===Teams===\n\n====By decade====\n\nThe most successful team of each decade, judged by number of Tipperary Senior Hurling Championship titles, is as follows:\n\n* 1890s: 3 for [[Boherlahen-Dualla GAA|Tubberadora]] (1895-96-98)\n* 1900s: 5 for [[Thurles Sarsfields GAA|Thurles Sarsfields]] (1904-06-07-08-09)\n* 1910s: 5 for [[Toomevara GAA|Toomevara]] (1910-12-13-14-19)\n* 1920s: 5 for [[Boherlahen-Dualla GAA|Boherlahen-Dualla]] (1922-24-25-27-28)\n* 1930s: 4 each for [[Moycarkey-Borris GAA|Moycarkey-Borris]] (1932-33-34-37) and [[Thurles Sarsfields GAA|Thurles Sarsfields]] (1935-36-38-39)\n* 1940s: 4 for [[Thurles Sarsfields GAA|Thurles Sarsfields]] (1942-44-45-46)\n* 1950s: 6 for [[Thurles Sarsfields GAA|Thurles Sarsfields]] (1952-55-56-57-58-59)\n* 1960s: 5 for [[Thurles Sarsfields GAA|Thurles Sarsfields]] (1961-62-63-64-65)\n* 1970s: 3 each for [[Roscrea GAA|Roscrea]] (1970-72-73) and [[Kilruane MacDonagh's GAA|Kilruane MacDonagh's]] (1977-78-79)\n* 1980s: 3 for [[Borris-Ileigh GAA|Borris-Ileigh]] (1981-83-86)\n* 1990s: 5 for [[Toomevara GAA|Toomevara]] (1992-93-94-98-99)\n* 2000s: 6 for [[Toomevara GAA|Toomevara]] (2000-01-03-04-06-08)\n* 2010s: 6 for [[Thurles Sarsfields GAA|Thurles Sarsfields]] (2010-12-14-15-16-17)\n\n====Gaps====\n\nTop ten longest gaps between successive championship titles:\n* 101 years: [[Clonoulty-Rossmore GAA|Clonoulty-Rossmore]] (1888-1989)\n* 55 years: [[Boherlahen-Dualla GAA|Boherlahen-Dualla]] (1941-1996)\n* 42 years: [[Moycarkey-Borris GAA|Moycarkey-Borris]] (1940-1982)\n* 36 years: [[Holycross-Ballycahill GAA|Holycross-Ballycahill]] (1954-1990)\n* 32 years: [[Toomevara GAA|Toomevara]] (1960-1992)\n* 31 years: [[Thurles Sarsfields GAA|Thurles Sarsfields]] (1974-2005)\n* 29 years: [[Toomevara GAA|Toomevara]] (1931-1960)\n* 28 years: [[Borris-Ileigh GAA|Borris-Ileigh]] (1953-1981)\n* 20 years: [[Toomevara GAA|Toomevara]] (1890-1910)\n* 19 years: [[Loughmore-Castleiney GAA|Loughmore-Castleiney]] (1988-2007)\n* 19 years: [[Moycarkey-Borris GAA|Moycarkey-Borris]] (1905-1926)\n\n===Top scorers===\n====Finals (1980-present)====\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!Final\n!Top scorer\n!Team\n!Score\n!Total\n|-\n|1980\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[Francis Loughnane]]\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[File:Colours of Cork.svg|border|20px]] [[Roscrea GAA|Roscrea]]\n|1-07\n|10\n|-\n|1981\n|style=\"text-align:left